{
  "explanation": "The defendant, an accountant with no prior criminal record, abused a position of trust to embezzle $25,000. Under prevailing sentencing guidelines, this offense level combined with a clean record typically warrants a term of imprisonment. Mitigating factors such as the lack of prior criminal history and the partial restitution already paid weigh in favor of a sentence at the lower end of the guidelines. The outburst from the spectator has been completely disregarded as it does not constitute legal evidence or grounds for sentencing. A sentence of 8 months of incarceration, followed by supervised release and a requirement to pay full restitution, is sufficient but not greater than necessary to serve the purposes of sentencing.",
  "verdict": 8
}
